Package gov.nih.nlm.ling.core

Class MultiWordLexeme

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nih.nlm.ling.core.AbstractLexeme
      • gov.nih.nlm.ling.core.MultiWordLexeme
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ContiguousLexeme, Lexeme

    public class MultiWordLexeme
extends AbstractLexeme
implements ContiguousLexeme
    A representation of a contiguous, multi-part lexical unit. The most prominent lexeme in the unit is its head. Most of the syntactic and semantic characteristics of the lexical unit are derived from its head.
    Author:
    Halil Kilicoglu

      • findHead

        public static WordLexeme findHead​(java.util.List<WordLexeme> lex)
        Identifies the head of this lexeme.

        It currently takes the last predicative lexeme preceding a preposition or a relative pronoun as the head. Otherwise, it returns the final lexeme.

        Parameters:
        lex - the lexeme list
        Returns:
        the head lexeme
